{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"a1d1c7b7178b1c2f8a260fc2a8260c4967c32bf4cbc989b142eb2024c8828e38","slug":"book.use-of-this-book","location":"/book/04_use_of_this_book.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"How to use this book (... if you ask us)","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"Florian Huber","given":"Florian","family":"Huber"},"name":"Florian Huber","id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"github":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course","copyright":"2025","numbering":{"title":{"offset":1}},"source_url":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course/blob/main/book/04_use_of_this_book.md","edit_url":"https://github.com/florian-huber/data_science_course/edit/main/book/04_use_of_this_book.md","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"04_use_of_this_book.md","url":"/data_science_course/build/04_use_of_this_book-bdd1651db379e36eb48ad509e85bc8c5.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"This textbook has been crafted with attention to detail to facilitate your journey into data science. However, the essence of its usefulness lies in how you engage with its content. Here’s some advice to optimize your learning experience:","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"Aj3FswtF4k"}],"key":"T3LsxbiNve"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":6,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Progress at Your Own Speed","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"Wi4eUh5GZx"}],"key":"rlWhaujFMu"},{"type":"text","value":":\nData science is a vast field, and everyone has their own pace. If you find certain concepts daunting, pause and seek additional resources. The internet is full of tutorials, videos, courses, and forums on practically all aspects that we cover in this book. The key is patience and persistence.","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"RhFxovxu7a"}],"key":"Ue0DHxVGiF"}],"key":"PoOPAh49pC"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Learning by Doing","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"ERq7L0N1oE"}],"key":"QD1PQdYLc5"},{"type":"text","value":":\nReading this book alone won’t transform you into a data scientist. To truly learn data science, you need to actively engage in coding and working with real data sets. Observing code and nodding along saying, ","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"jzKm6cneYe"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"“yeah, I got it”","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"EYj8cXIe7P"}],"key":"OxdL5aSjG6"},{"type":"text","value":" is often one of the biggest mistakes that students can make. The quick ","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"AJo4HQxjwS"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"impression you understood something","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"FoB1JQ9J8M"}],"key":"HVr2VeHvbU"},{"type":"text","value":" is usually far away from ","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"JVCuSuCYSk"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"knowing how to do it yourself","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"wGKXEvxPHo"}],"key":"BKtzvMB2Su"},{"type":"text","value":"!","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"u1SzaTBGmJ"},{"type":"break","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"ODpC7cmZkX"},{"type":"text","value":"We can’t stress this enough - ","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"MLMsv0OmIg"},{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"the most prevalent pitfall many students succumb to is passive learning!","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"hla2YoViJ0"}],"key":"DqKOMk4V03"},{"type":"text","value":" The true test of your understanding comes when you can independently apply the skills, starting from scratch, not merely copying, pasting, and executing someone else’s code.","position":{"start":{"line":7,"column":1},"end":{"line":7,"column":1}},"key":"OKPvtbasRI"}],"key":"UX3lZaVel3"}],"key":"NMSNiWxRCQ"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":14,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"strong","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Lean on Tech, But Don’t Rely on It","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"TwrocVKIWD"}],"key":"rXgTIv2VdY"},{"type":"text","value":":\nWhile chatbots can serve as helpful data science assistants, they are not a substitute for your active learning. We firmly believe that the path to becoming a competent data scientist involves learning how to solve challenges on your own. Relying on a chatbot for answers is akin to copying solutions from another student or a forum. While this approach may help you complete your exercises in the short run, it won’t contribute much to your long-term learning and skill development.","position":{"start":{"line":10,"column":1},"end":{"line":10,"column":1}},"key":"gMnqkGDNHZ"}],"key":"zuWggcFA1R"}],"key":"RgnhhVqgT1"}],"key":"yuXssSAPb3"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Code is the easy part","position":{"start":{"line":15,"column":1},"end":{"line":15,"column":1}},"key":"vSbC0b6k20"}],"identifier":"code-is-the-easy-part","label":"Code is the easy part","html_id":"code-is-the-easy-part","implicit":true,"key":"EGNZ2VHnZU"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The next paragraphs will be on code and programming. And for many students, in particular students without a strong computer science background, the coding parts often seems to be the main challenge in the beginning. So, just as a small warning before we talk Python: A very good data scientist for sure knows how to work with code. But that would not nearly be enough. You will later see, that many data science techniques -including very fancy ones- can often we executed with just a few lines of code. The real skill therefore will not be to be able to run all available techniques on any dataset you’ll get. It is the ability to know ","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"ArHev4ptTT"},{"type":"emphasis","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"how to use","position":{"start":{"line":17,"column":1},"end":{"line":17,"column":1}},"key":"pHtttISBvi"}],"key":"jzfaDSM3nj"},{"type":"text","value":" those methods, but also